    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "We already have online in-memory-pruning, which obviously is imperfect since it does not have access to all state, and never prunes stuff written to disk. \r\nWe also have offline disk-pruning, \r\nWe are not working on online pruning per se, BUT, when we switch trie schema to be path-based instead of hash-based, then our disk data will only represent one single trie. So essentially it will be pruned (x)\r\n\r\nMain PR: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/pull/25963 \r\n\r\nx: Caveat: we will actually not always clear storage elements from self-destructed accounts, so we will not achieve perfect pruning even with this approach. ",
